The tugboat in the foreground (above) is the P.S. JUMNA, a paddlewheel steam tugboat built in 1884. It operated in Littlehampton towing sailing ships in and out of the harbor, up until 1925. [<a href="http://www.thamestugs.co.uk/EARLY-TUG-NAMES-E-K.php" rel="nofollow">1</a>] &nbsp;The JUMNA famously appeared on numerous postcards of the day, and inspired many enthusiasts to build <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/8472006@N07/2085821949/">models</a> of her -- including this two-person miniature in Australia:

